A key promise in the campaign to leave the European Union was to make Britain more attractive to innovative digital companies by revolutionising the approach to data privacy and digital competition. Since Britain voted to leave the bloc, officials have worked on plans to give the country an edge over European rivals — hailed by ministers as more “pro-growth and innovation-friendly”. Insiders told Politico that the plummeting fortune of Mr Sunak - who has come under fire over his wife’s tax status and partygate fines - is particularly problematic given he was widely seen as a key advocate for tech at the top of government. A Government official working on tech policy said: “One of the things that I think is worrying is Sunak is in a very difficult position at the moment. We are just hoping he stays around really." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...